n. I have to study for my exam.\\\\nA: _______(2) _______(3) tomorrow night? Are you doing anything then?\\\\nB: No, I’m not. What have you got in mind?\\\\nA: I’m going to go bowling. _______(4) _______(5) _______(6) _______(7) come?\\\\nB: That _______(8) _______(9).\\\\nA: I’ll give you a ring at about five tomorrow.\\\\nB: OK, see you.","questionType":"LISTENING","options":[],"correctAnswer":"1:Shall | 2:How | 3:about | 4:Would | 5:you | 6:like | 7:to | 8:sounds | 9:nice","audioUrl":"https://res.cloudinary.com/dcz6avkds/video/upload/v1774710247/U1-09c-6_xxnbt9.mp3"},{"id":2922,"mongoQuestionId":"69c8f5771f0f44d8052a34b3","questionText":"1. My name is Tim.\\n2. My e-mail address is timr@gmail.com\\n3. I live in New York.\\n4. I have a reservation for tonight.","questionType":"SPEAKING","options":[],"correctAnswer":"","sampleAnswer":"","audioUrl":"https://res.cloudinary.com/dcz6avkds/video/upload/v1774506748/Tactics_for_Listening_Basic_CD1_05_kyct79.mp3"}]}]},{"treeId":5,"levelId":1,"nodes":[{"nodeId":21,"title":"Vocabulary","nodeType":"VOCAB","questions":[{"id":688,"mongoQuestionId":"69c8f30b1f0f44d8052a2b41","questionText":"Sophie ............................ have been ill today because she didn\'t come to school.","questionType":"VOCAB","options":["can\'t","should","must","would"],"correctAnswer":"must","audioUrl":""},{"id":799,"mongoQuestionId":"69c8f3101f0f44d8052a2bb0","questionText":"She often shops ........... .","questionType":"VOCAB","options":["display","remote","online"],"correctAnswer":"online","audioUrl":""},{"id":792,"mongoQuestionId":"69c8f3101f0f44d8052a2ba9","questionText":"A ufologist is someone ............ researches UFOs.","questionType":"VOCAB","options":["which","whose","who"],"correctAnswer":"who","audioUrl":""},{"id":693,"mongoQuestionId":"69c8f30b1f0f44d8052a2b46","questionText":"Do you have ............................ advice for someone who wants to become an inventor?","questionType":"VOCAB","options":["any","an","few","piece"],"correctAnswer":"any","audioUrl":""},{"id":759,"mongoQuestionId":"69c8f30e1f0f44d8052a2b88","questionText":"Danny and Tina live in a small ............ in the countryside.","questionType":"VOCAB","options":["cottage","castle","mansion"],"correctAnswer":"cottage","audioUrl":""},{"id":711,"mongoQuestionId":"69c8f30c1f0f44d8052a2b58","questionText":"Neither Alec ............................ Rob came to school today.","questionType":"VOCAB","options":["or","and","nor","either"],"correctAnswer":"nor","audioUrl":""},{"id":713,"mongoQuestionId":"69c8f30c1f0f44d8052a2b5a","questionText":"Jo hates mobiles, but Lorna is really addicted ............ hers: she won\'t go anywhere without it!","questionType":"VOCAB","options":["to","with","at","on"],"correctAnswer":"to","audioUrl":""},{"id":656,"mongoQuestionId":"69c8f3091f0f44d8052a2b21","questionText":"Which is more important – money or ............................ ?","questionType":"VOCAB","options":["environment","the environment","an environment","one environment"],"correctAnswer":"the environment","audioUrl":""},{"id":664,"mongoQuestionId":"69c8f3091f0f44d8052a2b29","questionText":"Even when he\'s very angry, my dad never ............................ or uses bad language.","questionType":"VOCAB","options":["swears","tells","whispers","broadcasts"],"correctAnswer":"swears","audioUrl":""},{"id":701,"mongoQuestionId":"69c8f30c1f0f44d8052a2b4e","questionText":"You ............................ help me, but you can if you want to.","questionType":"VOCAB","options":["don\'t have to","didn\'t need to","mustn\'t","haven\'t to"],"correctAnswer":"don\'t have to","audioUrl":""}]},{"nodeId":22,"title":"Listening","nodeType":"LISTENING","questions":[{"id":2807,"mongoQuestionId":"69c8f42f1f0f44d8052a33c0","questionText":"• Fantastic deals on package holidays in _______(1)\\\\n• _______(2)-week holidays on the Costa del Sol.\\\\n• A luxury _______(3) with full board.\\\\n• Cost of package, including flight, only _______(4) !\\\\nWe’re open 9 am – _______(5) pm.","questionType":"LISTENING","options":[],"correctAnswer":"1:Spain | 2:two | 3:hotel | 4:£269 | 5:6","audioUrl":"https://res.cloudinary.com/dcz6avkds/video/upload/v1774710252/U1-10-SA8_slot9x.mp3"}]},{"nodeId":23,"title":"Speaking","nodeType":"SPEAKING","questions":[{"id":2958,"mongoQuestionId":"69c8f57e1f0f44d8052a34d7","questionText":"ten\\neleven\\ntwelve\\nthirteen\\nfourteen\\nfifteen\\nsixteen\\nseventeen\\neighteen\\nnineteen\\ntwenty","questionType":"SPEAKING","options":[],"correctAnswer":"","audioUrl":"https://res.cloudinary.com/dcz6avkds/video/upload/v1774755968/U1-0Starter-04_h25d8b.mp3"}]},{"nodeId":24,"title":"Matching","nodeType":"MATCHING","questions":[{"id":3665,"mongoQuestionId":"69c8f6b11f0f44d8052a37ce","questionText":"benefit","questionType":"MATCHING","options":["MATCHING_PAIR"],"correctAnswer":"to get an advantage, or to give someone an advantage","audioUrl":""},{"id":3688,"mongoQuestionId":"69c8f6b31f0f44d8052a37e5","questionText":"upset","questionType":"MATCHING","options":["MATCHING_PAIR"],"correctAnswer":"to make someone feel sad, worried, or angry","audioUrl":""},{"id":3675,"mongoQuestionId":"69c8f6b31f0f44d8052a37d8","questionText":"stretch","questionType":"MATCHING","options":["MATCHING_PAIR"],"correctAnswer":"if you stretch something, or if it stretches, it becomes longer or wider when you pull it","audioUrl":""},{"id":3676,"mongoQuestionId":"69c8f6b31f0f44d8052a37d9","questionText":"tight","questionType":"MATCHING","options":["MATCHING_PAIR"],"correctAnswer":"fitting closely around your body or part of your body","audioUrl":""},{"id":3579,"mongoQuestionId":"69c8f6aa1f0f44d8052a3778","questionText":"throw away","questionType":"MATCHING","options":["MATCHING_PAIR"],"correctAnswer":"put sth in a rubbish bin","audioUrl":""},{"id":3618,"mongoQuestionId":"69c8f6ad1f0f44d8052a379f","questionText":"brain","questionType":"MATCHING","options":["MATCHING_PAIR"],"correctAnswer":"the organ inside your head that allows you to think and feel, and controls your body","audioUrl":""},{"id":3635,"mongoQuestionId":"69c8f6ae1f0f44d8052a37b0","questionText":"afford","questionType":"MATCHING","options":["MATCHING_PAIR"],"correctAnswer":"to have enough money to pay for something","audioUrl":""},{"id":3679,"mongoQuestionId":"69c8f6b31f0f44d8052a37dc","questionText":"locate","questionType":"MATCHING","options":["MATCHING_PAIR"],"correctAnswer":"to find out the exact place where someone or something is; be located: to exist in a particular place","audioUrl":""},{"id":3690,"mongoQuestionId":"69c8f6b31f0f44d8052a37e7","questionText":"doubt","questionType":"MATCHING","options":["MATCHING_PAIR"],"correctAnswer":"to think that something is probably not true, probably does not exist, or probably will not happen","audioUrl":""},{"id":3685,"mongoQuestionId":"69c8f6b31f0f44d8052a37e2","questionText":"feeling","questionType":"MATCHING","options":["MATCHING_PAIR"],"correctAnswer":"an emotional state, for example anger or happiness","audioUrl":""}]},{"nodeId":25,"title":"Review","nodeType":"REVIEW","questions":[{"id":73,"mongoQuestionId":"69c8f2ec1f0f44d8052a28da","questionText":"My sister loves watching TV, but I\'m not really ............ it: I much prefer reading a book.","questionType":"VOCAB","options":["up to","out of","in","into"],"correctAnswer":"into","audioUrl":""},{"id":94,"mongoQuestionId":"69c8f2ed1f0f44d8052a28ef","questionText":"I want to be a ........ so I can fly all over the world.","questionType":"VOCAB","options":["pilot","police officer","chef"],"correctAnswer":"pilot","audioUrl":""},{"id":726,"mongoQuestionId":"69c8f30d1f0f44d8052a2b67","questionText":"Environmental pollution causes ............ to people\'s health.","questionType":"VOCAB","options":["devastation","destruction","disaster","damage"],"correctAnswer":"damage","audioUrl":""},{"id":68,"mongoQuestionId":"69c8f2ec1f0f44d8052a28d5","questionText":"............................ on your jacket if you\'re cold.","questionType":"VOCAB","options":["Put","Take","Get","Add"],"correctAnswer":"Put","audioUrl":""},{"id":3262,"mongoQuestionId":"69c8f6991f0f44d8052a363b","questionText":"infection","questionType":"MATCHING","options":["MATCHING_PAIR"],"correctAnswer":"a disease that is caused by bacteria or by a virus","audioUrl":""},{"id":3242,"mongoQuestionId":"69c8f6981f0f44d8052a3627","questionText":"channel","questionType":"MATCHING","options":["MATCHING_PAIR"],"correctAnswer":"a television station and the programmes that it broadcasts","audioUrl":""},{"id":3451,"mongoQuestionId":"69c8f6a31f0f44d8052a36f8","questionText":"I often had to look","questionType":"MATCHING","options":["MATCHING_PAIR"],"correctAnswer":"after my younger sister when she was small.","audioUrl":""},{"id":3382,"mongoQuestionId":"69c8f69f1f0f44d8052a36b3","questionText":"swear","questionType":"MATCHING","options":["MATCHING_PAIR"],"correctAnswer":"to use words that are deliberately offensive, for example because you are angry","audioUrl":""},{"id":2787,"mongoQuestionId":"69c8f42e1f0f44d8052a33ac","questionText":"A: How was your dinner, Evan?\\\\nB: It _______(1) delicious! How about yours?\\\\nA: Actually, it _______(2) _______(3). My vegetables were overcooked.\\\\nB: Really?\\\\nA: Yeah, and the potatoes weren\'t _______(4) enough.\\\\nB: Oh, that\'s too bad. And you know, the service _______(5) _______(6) _______(7) fast as it usually is here.\\\\nA: Yeah, I guess you\'re right. Let\'s eat somewhere else next time.","questionType":"LISTENING","options":[],"correctAnswer":"1:was | 2:wasn\'t | 3:great | 4:spicy | 5:wasn\'t | 6:as | 7:as","audioUrl":"https://res.cloudinary.com/dcz6avkds/video/upload/v1774446140/Tactics_for_Listening_Basic_CD2_28_nfxsu0.mp3"},{"id":2942,"mongoQuestionId":"69c8f57a1f0f44d8052a34c7","questionText":"1. It\'s a noisy city.\\r\\n2. It\'s very crowded.\\r\\n3. Everything is cheap.\\r\\n4. The parks are beautiful.","questionType":"SPEAKING","options":[],"correctAnswer":"","audioUrl":"https://res.cloudinary.com/d